What is \(\wp(\emptyset)\) ? Show Answer \(\wp(\emptyset) = \{\emptyset\}\) . Suppose that \(A=\{1, 2, 3\}\) , \(B=\{2, 3, 4\}\) and \(C=\{1, 2, 4, 6\}\) . Find the following sets: \((A\cap B)\cup C\) \((A\cup B)\setminus (A\cup C)\) \((A\cup B)\Delta (A\cup C)\) \((A\cup B)\setminus (A\cap B)\) \(A\cap (B\cup C)\) Show Answer \((A\cap B)\cup C=\{2, 3\} \cup \{1, 2, 4, 6\} = \{1, 2, 3, 4, 6\}\) \((A\cup B)\setminus (A\cup C) = \{1, 2, 3, 4\}\setminus \{ 1, 2, 3, 4, 6\} = \varnothing\) \((A\cup C)\setminus (A\cup B) = \{ 1, 2, 3, 4, 6\}\setminus \{1, 2, 3, 4\} = \{6\}\) \((A\cup B)\Delta (A\cup C) = \varnothing\cup \{6\}=\{6\}\) \((A\cup B)\setminus (A\cap B) = \{1, 2, 3, 4\}\setminus \{2, 3\}=\{1, 4\}\) \(A\cap (B\cup C) = \{1, 2, 3\} \cap \{1,2, 3,4, 6\}=\{1,2,3\}\) Suppose that \(A=\{1\}\) and $B={1, 3}. True or False: \(1\subseteq A\) . True or False: \(1\in A\cap B\) . True or False: \(1 \in \{A,B\}\) . True or False: \(\{2\}\in A\cap B\) . True or False: \(\{2\}\subseteq A\cap B\) . Show Answer \(1\subseteq A\) is False: \(1\) is an element of \(A\) , but not a subset of \(A\) . \(1\in A\cap B\) is True: \(A\cap B=\{1\}\) , so \(1\in\{1\} = A\cap B\) . \(1 \in \{A,B\}\) is False: \(\{A,B\}=\{\{1\}, \{2,3\}\}\) , and \(1
ot\in \{\{1\}, \{2,3\}\}\) . (Note that we do have that \(\{1\}\in\{A,B\}\) and of course \(1\in\{1\}\) .) \(\{2\}\in A\cap B\) is False: \(A\cap B=\{1\}\) which does not contain \(2\) . \(\{2\}\subseteq A\cap B\) is False: Since \(2
